<plot>It seems like an abundance of possibilities. After screening the newspaper, there are five interesting job openings. Surely one of them must be to her taste. An interviewee goes to a job interview at five different companies, but those bosses are all the same. All they want is an employee who does everything by herself (so they can sit and do nothing) and who, preferably, doesn't require any health insurance to be paid for. This is getting really frustrating.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?055776</url></doc>
